and timid does swam on the surging seas.
The yellow Tiber we have seen, with waves hurled back from Tuscan shores, rushing in fury to bear down old Numa's kingly monuments and Vesta's holy shrine:
while the fond river glories to avenge the too complaining Ilia, and sweeps in torrents o'er his left-hand bank, though Jove approve it not.
