That man had heart encased in oak and brass of triple folds who first committed to the savage deep his brittle bark, nor feared the squally sou-west battling with the north, nor yet the gloomy Hyades, and raging force of Notus, than whom no sterner tyrant lords it over Hadria's waves, whether he wills to raise or lull by calm, the narrow seas.
In what shape would he fear grim death's approach, who, with a tearless eye, was wont to view the hideous forms of floating monsters and gaze upon the heaving deep, and those Ceraunian rocks of ill-repute ?
